{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀληθ-ής</b> [ᾰ], <br /> <i>Doric dialect</i> ἀλᾱθής, ές, (λήθω, ={λανθάνω}: ἀληθὲς τὸ μὴ λήθῃ ὑποπῖπτον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Magnum” 62.51)\">Refs</a>]:—<b>unconcealed</b>, so <b>true, real</b>, opposed to <b>false, apparent</b>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, opposed to ψευδής,in phrases ἀληθέα μυθήσασθαι, εἰπεῖν, ἀγορεύειν, ἀληθὲς ἐνισπεῖν, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.382, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.254, 3.254, 247, +others; in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus and _Attic dialect_ τὸ ἀληθές, by Trag. crasis τἀληθές, _Ionic dialect_ τὠληθές (5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.68, 69), or τὰ ἀληθῆ, by crasis τἀληθῆ, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀληθέϊ λόγῳ χρᾶσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.14, etc.; οἱ ἀληθέϊ λόγῳ βασιλέες 1.120; ἀληθεστάτη πρόφασις 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.23. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> of persons, etc., <b>truthful, honest</b> (not in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, see below), ἀ. νόος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 2.92; κατήγορος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 439; κριτής 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.56\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἶνος ἀ. `<b>in vino veritas</b>', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 217e; ὁ μέσος ἀ. τις 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1108a20. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> of oracles, <b>true, unerring</b>, ἀλαθέα μαντίων θῶκον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.6, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 993, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1537 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of dreams, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 710. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of qualities or events, <b>true, real</b>, φίλος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 424; ἀ. τὸ πραχθέν 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.6\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>genuine</b>, ἀ. εἶναι δεῖ τὸ σεμνόν, οὐ κενόν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 596. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>realizing itself, coming to fulfilment</b>, ἀρά[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 944. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> ἀληθῶς, <i>Ionic dialect</i> -θέως, <b>truly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 5.1, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.11, +others, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 315, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.b</b></Level4> <b>actually, in reality</b>, γένος τόδε Ζηνός ἐστιν ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 585; ἀ. οὐδὲν ἐξῃκασμένα [prev. author] “Ag.” 1244, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.22, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν ἀ. μουσικήν (i.e. οὖσαν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 209.6:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —ὡς ἀ. <b>in the true way, really</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 739, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 63a, etc.; ἡ μὲν γὰρ ὡς ἀ. μήτηρ 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.149\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-εστέρως</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 347e,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>-έστερον</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.4\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> <b>-έστατα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.8.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <i>neuter</i> as <i>adverb</i>, <i>proparoxytone</i> ἄληθε; <b>indeed? really?</b> ironically, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 350, “Ant.” 758, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 241, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 840, “Av.” 174. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> τὸ ἀληθές <b>truly</b>, <i>Ionic dialect</i> τὠληθές[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 7.70. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> <b>not forgetting, careful</b>, γυνὴ χερνῆτις ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.433, compare 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 24.233\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—the sense <b>honest</b> is post- [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>ἀληθ-ίζω</b>, <b>dye with genuine purple,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PHolm. 18.6. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i> -ίζομαι, ={ἀληθεύω}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.136, 3.72, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.230b, 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.39, 59.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0227","accentedUnicode":"ἀληθής","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0225","matchingForm":"ἀλήθεια","stepTransliteration":"alētheia","gloss":"truth","_zh_tw_Gloss":"真理","_es_Gloss":"verdad","_zh_Gloss":"真理"},{"strongNumber":"G0226","matchingForm":"ἀληθεύω","stepTransliteration":"alētheuō","gloss":"be truthful","_zh_tw_Gloss":"說真理","_es_Gloss":"ser honesto","_zh_Gloss":"说真理"},{"strongNumber":"G0228","matchingForm":"ἀληθινός","stepTransliteration":"alēthinos","gloss":"true","_zh_tw_Gloss":"真實","_es_Gloss":"verdadero","_zh_Gloss":"真实"},{"strongNumber":"G0230","matchingForm":"ἀληθῶς","stepTransliteration":"alēthōs","gloss":"truly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"真實地","_es_Gloss":"verd